warfarin_vitamin_k.title: Vitamin K Content (Warfarin Interaction)
warfarin_vitamin_k.description: High vitamin K content may reduce warfarin effectiveness. Maintain consistent intake if on blood thinners.

maoi_tyramine.title: Tyramine Content (MAOI Interaction)
maoi_tyramine.description: CRITICAL: Tyramine can cause dangerous blood pressure spikes with MAOI medications. This interaction can be fatal.

grapefruit_cyp3a4.title: Grapefruit Interaction (CYP3A4)
grapefruit_cyp3a4.description: Grapefruit affects how 85+ medications are metabolized. Can increase drug levels to dangerous amounts.

ace_potassium.title: High Potassium (ACE Inhibitor/ARB Interaction)
ace_potassium.description: High potassium foods can interact with ACE inhibitors and ARBs, potentially causing dangerous potassium levels.

calcium_antibiotics.title: Calcium Content (Antibiotic Interaction)
calcium_antibiotics.description: Calcium can reduce absorption of certain antibiotics. Take medication 2 hours before or 6 hours after calcium-rich foods.

allergen_milk.title: Milk/Dairy Allergen
allergen_milk.description: Contains milk or dairy products. One of the top 9 allergens.

allergen_eggs.title: Egg Allergen
allergen_eggs.description: Contains eggs or egg products. One of the top 9 allergens.

allergen_peanuts.title: Peanut Allergen
allergen_peanuts.description: Contains peanuts. One of the top 9 allergens. Can cause severe anaphylaxis.

allergen_tree_nuts.title: Tree Nut Allergen
allergen_tree_nuts.description: Contains tree nuts. One of the top 9 allergens.

allergen_fish.title: Fish Allergen
allergen_fish.description: Contains fish. One of the top 9 allergens.

allergen_shellfish.title: Shellfish Allergen
allergen_shellfish.description: Contains shellfish (crustaceans or mollusks). One of the top 9 allergens.

allergen_wheat.title: Wheat/Gluten Allergen
allergen_wheat.description: Contains wheat or gluten. One of the top 9 allergens. Harmful for celiac disease.

allergen_soy.title: Soy Allergen
allergen_soy.description: Contains soy products. One of the top 9 allergens.

ckd_high_potassium.title: High Potassium (Kidney Disease)
ckd_high_potassium.description: High potassium content. People with kidney disease may need to limit potassium intake.

ckd_high_phosphorus.title: High Phosphorus (Kidney Disease)
ckd_high_phosphorus.description: High phosphorus content. People with kidney disease may need to limit phosphorus intake.

ckd_high_sodium.title: High Sodium (Kidney/Heart Disease)
ckd_high_sodium.description: May contain high sodium. People with kidney or heart disease should limit sodium.

immuno_raw_eggs.title: Raw/Undercooked Eggs (Immunocompromised Risk)
immuno_raw_eggs.description: May contain raw or undercooked eggs. Risk of Salmonella for immunocompromised individuals.

immuno_raw_meat.title: Raw/Undercooked Meat (Immunocompromised Risk)
immuno_raw_meat.description: May contain raw or undercooked meat. Risk of bacterial infection for immunocompromised individuals.

immuno_raw_seafood.title: Raw/Undercooked Seafood (Immunocompromised Risk)
immuno_raw_seafood.description: May contain raw or undercooked seafood. Risk of Vibrio, Listeria for immunocompromised individuals.

immuno_unpasteurized.title: Unpasteurized Dairy (Immunocompromised Risk)
immuno_unpasteurized.description: May contain unpasteurized dairy. Risk of Listeria for pregnant women and immunocompromised individuals.

immuno_sprouts.title: Raw Sprouts (Immunocompromised Risk)
immuno_sprouts.description: Raw sprouts can harbor bacteria. Risk for immunocompromised individuals.

diabetic_high_glycemic.title: High Glycemic Index
diabetic_high_glycemic.description: High glycemic food that may cause rapid blood sugar spikes. Monitor portions if diabetic.

alcohol_content.title: Contains Alcohol
alcohol_content.description: Recipe contains alcohol. Some may cook off during preparation, but trace amounts may remain.

caffeine_content.title: Contains Caffeine
caffeine_content.description: Contains caffeine. May affect sleep, anxiety, or interact with some medications.

goitrogen_thyroid.title: Goitrogen Content (Thyroid Consideration)
goitrogen_thyroid.description: Contains goitrogens which may affect thyroid function in large amounts. Usually safe when cooked.

histamine_intolerance.title: High Histamine Content
histamine_intolerance.description: High in histamine or histamine-releasing. May trigger symptoms in histamine-intolerant individuals.

fodmap_high.title: High FODMAP Content
fodmap_high.description: High in FODMAPs. May trigger IBS symptoms. Consider low-FODMAP alternatives.
